N2  - Approximately two hundred books on mathematical programming have been published during the past eight years. Most workers in this field have immediate access to only a minor fraction of these, but would have at least vicarious access to many of the rest through book reviews if only they knew where to look. That is the primary motivation for this bibliography of book reviews published during the years 1965?1972. A secondary reason is simply to furnish a reasonably comprehensive list of recent books on mathematical programming.
